into the number two spot.

772
01:01:32,856 --> 01:01:36,553
And out of nowhere, Kate Moseley
and Doug Dorsey grab number three.

773
01:01:36,760 --> 01:01:38,523
Two couples are all
the United States...

774
01:01:38,728 --> 01:01:40,719
...are allowed to send
to the olympic Games.

775
01:01:40,931 --> 01:01:44,492
Tomorrow night's long program
should be very exciting.

776
01:01:44,701 --> 01:01:46,931
Man, this overnight thing is brutal.

777
01:01:47,137 --> 01:01:48,604
Why can't it be a double-header?

778
01:01:48,805 --> 01:01:51,000
Short program, long program,
same night.

779
01:01:51,241 --> 01:01:52,765
We're out of here.
Know what I mean?

780
01:01:52,976 --> 01:01:53,965
I know what you mean.

781
01:01:54,177 --> 01:01:57,146
It's like, enough already. It's like....

782
01:01:57,514 --> 01:01:58,811
What's the word?

783
01:01:59,015 --> 01:02:00,642
You know what word
I'm looking for?

784
01:02:00,851 --> 01:02:02,375
I don't know. Expectation?

785
01:02:02,586 --> 01:02:04,816
-No, no. When you....
-Anticipation?

786
01:02:05,021 --> 01:02:06,079
-Excitement?
-Foreplay.

787
01:02:08,191 --> 01:02:10,682
-Foreplay?
-Yeah, you know. Like foreplay.

788
01:02:10,894 --> 01:02:12,088
Yeah, I know what it means.

789
01:02:12,295 --> 01:02:14,559
Well, wouldn't you rather
just get right to it?

790
01:02:14,764 --> 01:02:16,755
-What?
-Skating.

791
01:02:16,967 --> 01:02:18,901
Long program.

792
01:02:19,503 --> 01:02:22,165
Chicago. Nationals.

793
01:02:22,706 --> 01:02:24,230
Flowers?

794
01:02:27,544 --> 01:02:28,704
Sleep.

795
01:02:28,912 --> 01:02:30,402
I'd rather sleep.

796
01:02:34,718 --> 01:02:35,980
Sleep?

