-Fantastic.
-Are those for me?

808
01:03:40,817 --> 01:03:42,444
Hey. You were great.

809
01:03:44,588 --> 01:03:46,715
5. 4, 5. 4, 5. 4....

810
01:03:46,923 --> 01:03:49,483
These are not great marks.
I expected much higher.

811
01:03:49,693 --> 01:03:51,160
Evidently, so did the crowd.

812
01:03:51,494 --> 01:03:53,724
It's hard to explain
to people outside the sport...

813
01:03:53,930 --> 01:03:56,922
...but sometimes the scores
reflect more than what's on the ice.

814
01:03:57,133 --> 01:03:58,794
The judges have their favorites...

815
01:03:59,002 --> 01:04:01,596
...and they obviously don't include
Moseley and Dorsey.

816
01:04:01,805 --> 01:04:04,638
It looks like the Weidermans will join
Neuman and Pekurovsky...

817
01:04:04,841 --> 01:04:06,968
...on the olympic team.

818
01:04:09,012 --> 01:04:10,479
This is horseshit.

819
01:04:10,680 --> 01:04:14,446
What crap are they trying to pull?
We skated our asses off out there.

820
01:04:14,651 --> 01:04:16,084
You call this a sport?

821
01:04:16,286 --> 01:04:17,878
Bullshit.

822
01:05:01,865 --> 01:05:05,301
Just terrible. She stepped into
the spin, then I'm not sure...

823
01:05:05,502 --> 01:05:08,960
...but it looked like she got caught
in his lederhosen.

824
01:05:09,172 --> 01:05:11,470
You know what this means.

825
01:05:14,010 --> 01:05:15,841
We are in.

826
01:05:17,514 --> 01:05:20,381
Yeah. Yeah. We're going to France.

827
01:05:20,583 --> 01:05:22,175
Parlez-vous Olympics?

828
01:05:25,088 --> 01:05:26,487
Sure you wanna do this?

829
01:05:26,690 --> 01:05:28,419
