01:07:10,627 --> 01:07:13,152
All right. We're here.

831
01:07:15,598 --> 01:07:17,088
Oh, boy.

832
01:07:19,435 --> 01:07:21,300
Okay.

833
01:07:28,611 --> 01:07:29,635
Wanna dance?

834
01:07:29,846 --> 01:07:31,177
No, I don't think so.

835
01:07:31,381 --> 01:07:32,871
Doug.

836
01:07:33,883 --> 01:07:35,680
Douglas, you silly thing.

837
01:07:35,885 --> 01:07:38,012
Please don't think.

838
01:07:39,589 --> 01:07:43,025
That's what I like about the way I feel.
Even if I tried to think, I couldn't.

839
01:07:43,226 --> 01:07:47,287
And I think too much,
and I think so long. And it's so tiring.

840
01:07:47,497 --> 01:07:51,160
The world is spinning
and spinning and spinning.

841
01:07:52,869 --> 01:07:54,598
Look....

842
01:07:57,440 --> 01:07:59,101
Did you ever play with magnets?

843
01:07:59,309 --> 01:08:01,106
You used to have to
push them around...

844
01:08:01,311 --> 01:08:04,007
...and they'd push away and
you push them around the table?

845
01:08:04,214 --> 01:08:09,049
All you really had to do was
just flip them over, and suddenly....

846
01:08:16,292 --> 01:08:19,056
Don't you see? That's why
everything's been so awful.

847
01:08:19,262 --> 01:08:20,957
All we needed was a little flip.

848
01:08:21,164 --> 01:08:22,927
Kate, it's not right.
What about Hale?

849
01:08:23,132 --> 01:08:25,532
Oh, Hale shmale.

850
01:08:27,103 --> 01:08:28,161
We're through.

851
01:08:31,040 --> 01:08:34,134
Our engagement is off.

852
01:08:34,510 --> 01:08:36,068
Flip.

853
01:08:57,033 --> 01:08:58,625
Come on. Not tonight.

854
01:08:58,835 --> 01:09:00,132
Not like this.

855
01:09:00,336 --> 01:09:02,236
Not like what?

856
01:09:04,307 --> 01:09:06,172
Not like me?

857
01:09:07,377 --> 01:09:10,369
-Kate, you're bombed.
-What do you mean?

858
01:09:11,481 --> 01:09:14,382
That means that it's time
for you to go to bed.

859
01:09:14,584 --> 01:09:15,812
God, just what I need.

860
01:09:16,019 --> 01:09:18,112
Someone else telling me what to do.

861
01:09:18,321 --> 01:09:21,757
In case you've missed it,
I am throwing myself at you.

862
01:09:21,958 --> 01:09:23,619
I am tearing off my clothes...

863
01:09:23,826 --> 01:09:26,818
...and you are giving me a rundown
on drinking dos and don'ts.

864
01:09:27,030 --> 01:09:28,588
Kate, why don't you calm--

865
01:09:28,798 --> 01:09:30,493
I get enough coaching
on the ice. Get out.

866
01:09:30,700 --> 01:09:33,567
-You've got this all wrong.
-Do I ever.

867
01:09:34,904 --> 01:09:38,601
Excuse my surprise, but really,
what a disappointment.

868
01:09:39,375 --> 01:09:42,435
-What is that supposed to mean?
-Well, look at you.

869
01:09:43,246 --> 01:09:45,544
God's gift to reckless abandon...

870
01:09:45,748 --> 01:09:49,309
...revealed as nothing but a prude
in wolf's clothing.

871
01:09:51,287 --> 01:09:53,278
You're a lousy drunk.

872
01:09:53,489 --> 01:09:55,514
And you're a lousy date.

873
01:09:59,896 --> 01:10:01,864
It didn't have to be like this.

874
01:10:03,299 --> 01:10:05,062
I said, get out.

875
01:10:48,211 --> 01:10:49,803
Hi.

876
01:10:50,313 --> 01:10:52,281
I watched your program.

877
01:10:52,482 --> 01:10:55,246
You've got a great sit spin.

878
01:10:57,487 --> 01:11:01,116
I thought maybe
we could trade secrets.

879
01:11:52,341 --> 01:11:54,832
It's a little early for practice, isn't it?

880
01:11:55,211 --> 01:11:56,838
I'm sorry. I must have
the wrong room.

881
01:11:57,046 --> 01:11:59,514
Ask her for more towels, will you?

882
01:12:11,160 --> 01:12:12,593
Kate.

883
01:12:13,196 --> 01:12:14,788
Kate.

884
01:12:14,997 --> 01:12:16,988
Kate, will you wait a minute? Kate.

885
01:12:17,200 --> 01:12:18,758
Kate.

886
01:12:18,968 --> 01:12:20,333
Kate.

887
01:12:20,536 --> 01:12:21,935
-Kate.
-Don't. Don't even try it.

888
01:12:22,138 --> 01:12:23,628
Just looking at you makes me sick.

889
01:12:23,840 --> 01:12:25,637
To think I was coming to apologize.

890
01:12:26,242 --> 01:12:27,368
Lorie Pekurovsky.

891
01:12:27,577 --> 01:12:29,875
Were you or were you not engaged
until last night?

892
01:12:30,079 --> 01:12:32,274
-Hardly the point.
-You threw me out of your room.

893
01:12:32,482 --> 01:12:34,143
She may not have
waited much longer.

894
01:12:34,350 --> 01:12:36,784
-That's not how it happened.
-Spare me the details.

895
01:12:36,986 --> 01:12:38,510
-Where the hell do you get off?
-Me?

896
01:12:38,721 --> 01:12:39,813
This is my fault?

897
01:12:40,022 --> 01:12:42,650
From the first day, you treated me
like a hired hand.

898
01:12:42,859 --> 01:12:46,454
Then one night you get drunk,
I'm supposed to thank my lucky stars?

899
01:12:46,662 --> 01:12:48,823
I'm sorry. I don't downshift that fast.

900
01:12:49,031 --> 01:12:51,932
-Get out of my way.
-No problem.

901
01:12:52,135 --> 01:12:55,229
I've been practicing that move
for a year and a half.

902
01:13:00,743 --> 01:13:02,301
Blind date.

903
01:13:02,645 --> 01:13:03,746
So we have little problem, da?

904
01:13:03,746 --> 01:13:05,611
So we have little problem, da?

905
01:13:07,049 --> 01:13:10,018
Good. We skip little problem...

906
01:13:10,219 --> 01:13:13,814
...and go straight line
to big problem.

907
01:13:14,824 --> 01:13:18,851
"And what is big problem, coach?"

908
01:13:19,061 --> 01:13:21,996
Smilkov and Brushkin.

909
01:13:22,598 --> 01:13:23,758
"Who?"

910
01:13:23,966 --> 01:13:27,367
Smilkov and Brushkin.

911
01:13:28,104 --> 01:13:30,629
Last night they win
European Championship.

912
01:13:31,140 --> 01:13:33,199
Perfect scores.

913
01:13:33,576 --> 01:13:37,842
Everybody's been blown away.
Contest is over.

914
01:13:38,047 --> 01:13:41,539
Smilkov and Brushkin
are unbeatable.

915
01:13:41,984 --> 01:13:45,977
So hello Soviet surprise package.

916
01:13:46,189 --> 01:13:48,714
Goodbye gold medal.

917
01:13:49,892 --> 01:13:53,487
Of course, there is possible solution.

918
01:13:53,696 --> 01:13:58,793
But it's probably too dangerous.

919
01:14:10,346 --> 01:14:11,506
Where did these come from?

920
01:14:11,714 --> 01:14:13,477
For 20 years
I've been working on this.

921
01:14:13,683 --> 01:14:19,019
But you know, to have skaters,
to have situation, to have desire...

922
01:14:19,488 --> 01:14:20,819
...is not ready until now.

923
01:14:21,023 --> 01:14:24,424
What is this?
Is this a bounce spin into a throw?

924
01:14:25,661 --> 01:14:28,186
-You can't do that.
-The key to this is release.

925
01:14:28,397 --> 01:14:29,455
There can be no halfway.

926
01:14:29,665 --> 01:14:32,896
No. No. It's illegal.

927
01:14:34,670 --> 01:14:36,968
Is gray area.

928
01:14:37,173 --> 01:14:40,734
Bounce spin to a throw twist.
Then I catch her?

929
01:14:40,943 --> 01:14:42,740
Well, sort of.

930
01:14:43,713 --> 01:14:44,941
We can't do this.

931
01:14:45,147 --> 01:14:47,240
Why not? We have all the pieces.

932
01:14:47,450 --> 01:14:49,509
We have five weeks.

933
01:14:49,719 --> 01:14:51,186
The Pamchenko Twist.

934
01:14:52,521 --> 01:14:54,989
-Absolutely not.
-Expect us to name it after you?

935
01:14:55,191 --> 01:14:57,091
No, no. Is mistake.

936
01:14:57,293 --> 01:14:59,887
-ls not right time.
-This is good stuff. I can do this.

937
01:15:00,096 --> 01:15:02,462
-What are you saying? I can't?
-Hey, if the shoe fits.

938
01:15:02,932 --> 01:15:05,332
Hey, listen. I have been
competing for 1 3 years...

939
01:15:05,534 --> 01:15:09,231
...and nobody tells me
what I can or cannot do.

940
01:15:14,110 --> 01:15:16,374
Don't quit your day job.

941
01:15:20,916 --> 01:15:22,042
Okay, again.

942
01:15:23,386 --> 01:15:24,580
Again.

943
01:15:24,787 --> 01:15:25,754
Again, again.

944
01:15:25,955 --> 01:15:27,616
Again. Again.

945
01:15:31,527 --> 01:15:33,290
Katya, head up.

946
01:15:33,496 --> 01:15:37,159
Higher. Higher. She has to fly.

947
01:15:43,005 --> 01:15:46,031
-Are they gonna get it?
-Eventually.

948
01:15:46,242 --> 01:15:47,903
Before they kill each other?

949
01:15:51,881 --> 01:15:53,610
Release. Release must be total.

950
01:15:53,816 --> 01:15:55,943
Is no halfway. Halfway is bullshit.

951
01:15:56,152 --> 01:15:58,586
You go halfway, you get hurt.

952
01:16:08,030 --> 01:16:09,520
Higher.

953
01:16:09,732 --> 01:16:11,563
Much higher.

954
01:16:12,368 --> 01:16:15,303
We are needing an explosion.

955
01:16:50,239 --> 01:16:51,638
Kate?

956
01:16:53,142 --> 01:16:55,838
I was just looking at
the pictures of mother.

957
01:17:01,717 --> 01:17:03,275
I can hear her now:

958
01:17:03,486 --> 01:17:04,680
"The Olympics."

959
01:17:07,556 --> 01:17:09,387
It's what she always dreamed of.

960
01:17:11,627 --> 01:17:12,958
Look at this thing.

961
01:17:13,429 --> 01:17:15,056
Just sitting here empty.

962
01:17:17,833 --> 01:17:19,926
We're almost there, honey.

963
01:17:20,669 --> 01:17:21,931
I can taste it.

964
01:17:22,138 --> 01:17:24,197
What if it stays empty?

965
01:17:24,407 --> 01:17:25,635
Not this time.

966
01:17:26,308 --> 01:17:28,902
-Go to bed. You need your rest.
-I'm not tired.

967
01:17:29,111 --> 01:17:30,373
-Kate.
-No.

968
01:17:31,447 --> 01:17:33,415
What are we doing?

969
01:17:35,618 --> 01:17:37,916
Why am I doing this?

970
01:17:39,422 --> 01:17:41,390
It's what you've always wanted.

971
01:17:42,291 --> 01:17:43,724
Always?

972
01:17:47,129 --> 01:17:49,597
-Kate--
-I know.

973
01:17:50,266 --> 01:17:51,426
I'm going.

974
01:17:51,634 --> 01:17:55,035
These little pep-talks
can be so exhausting.

975
01:18:40,783 --> 01:18:42,580
Opening ceremonies,
you enjoyed yourself?

976
01:18:42,785 --> 01:18:44,776
-Oh, it was great.
-Cold and great.

977
01:18:44,987 --> 01:18:48,753
So, Doug, what's the difference
between this and hockey?

978
01:18:48,958 --> 01:18:50,357
The women.

979
01:18:50,860 --> 01:18:53,294
What's the feeling?
Everybody out for themselves...

980
01:18:53,496 --> 01:18:56,260
