01:20:00,596 --> 01:20:01,995
Enough.

998
01:20:09,572 --> 01:20:11,164
Button it.

999
01:20:11,674 --> 01:20:13,232
We're on.

1000
01:20:15,177 --> 01:20:16,804
Good luck.

1001
01:20:20,783 --> 01:20:23,013
Representing the United States
of America...

1002
01:20:23,218 --> 01:20:24,185
...Moseley and Dorsey.

1003
01:20:24,386 --> 01:20:27,184
-Button the goddamn button.
-Get over it.

1004
01:20:27,389 --> 01:20:29,983
You are an immature asshole
of the lowest order.

1005
01:20:31,260 --> 01:20:33,421
If it was 40 below and that button...

1006
01:20:33,629 --> 01:20:35,756
...meant the difference
between a long life...

1007
01:20:35,965 --> 01:20:37,865
...and a horrible death
from hypothermia...

1008
01:20:38,067 --> 01:20:40,627
...I still wouldn't give you
the satisfaction.

1009
01:20:41,503 --> 01:20:42,470
Skate.

1010
01:21:06,729 --> 01:21:08,162
A technically superior program...

1011
01:21:08,364 --> 01:21:10,457
...but did you feel
there was something missing?

1012
01:21:10,666 --> 01:21:13,567
Absolutely. They delivered all
the short-program required moves...

1013
01:21:13,769 --> 01:21:15,100
...but it seemed very cold.

1014
01:21:15,304 --> 01:21:18,330
As if we were seeing two strangers,
rather than a fluid pair.

1015
01:21:19,375 --> 01:21:22,242
It just didn't look like
they were having fun out there.

1016
01:21:24,847 --> 01:21:26,212
Hey, Doug...

1017
01:21:26,415 --> 01:21:29,282
-...was the altitude a problem tonight?
-No.

1018
01:21:31,086 --> 01:21:34,613
Long program. We've been hearing all
week about your new surprise move.

1019
01:21:34,823 --> 01:21:37,314
-What's it called?
-The Pamchenko.

1020
01:21:37,526 --> 01:21:40,359
-The Pamchenko. Is it named after--?
-We're not doing it.

1021
01:21:40,562 --> 01:21:42,587
-What?
-We're taking it out of the program.

1022
01:21:42,798 --> 01:21:44,493
It's not ready.

1023
01:21:45,367 --> 01:21:46,698
Doug?

1024
01:21:48,771 --> 01:21:50,295
A button?

1025
01:21:50,506 --> 01:21:52,371
-What in hell are you thinking of?
-Me?

1026
01:21:52,574 --> 01:21:54,405
Yes, you. What the hell
is in your head?

1027
01:21:54,610 --> 01:21:56,100
He's making like this is my fault.

1028
01:21:56,311 --> 01:21:58,711
You didn't deliver.
What, you want a pat on the back?

1029
01:21:58,914 --> 01:22:00,677
When did I become
the designated asshole?

1030
01:22:00,883 --> 01:22:02,282
What happened?
Ask the ice queen.

1031
01:22:02,518 --> 01:22:04,782
-Enough of that.
-When you're done, Jack...

1032
01:22:04,987 --> 01:22:09,424
...you can tell me why I spent 5 weeks
on a move she was never gonna do.

1033
01:22:09,625 --> 01:22:11,650
-You're out of line.
-I needed the gold medal.

1034
01:22:11,860 --> 01:22:13,657
Forget it.
We can win without the move.

1035
01:22:13,862 --> 01:22:16,695
-lmpossible.
-Where the hell were you during this?

1036
01:22:16,899 --> 01:22:19,197
Where was l? I was babysitting.

1037
01:22:19,401 --> 01:22:22,063
Loud and clear, folks:
Losing gracefully does nothing for me.

1038
01:22:22,271 --> 01:22:26,071
-Think about that in the future.
-That what you told Brian in Calgary?

1039
01:22:28,143 --> 01:22:31,044
You can kid all you want about
what happened. I've seen the tapes.

1040
01:22:31,246 --> 01:22:33,043
Brian was getting it done.

1041
01:22:33,482 --> 01:22:35,677
Ask him. He'll tell you.

1042
01:22:36,218 --> 01:22:37,947
All right, Douglas, is enough.

1043
01:22:38,153 --> 01:22:39,381
Today it's about a button.

1044
01:22:39,588 --> 01:22:42,056
You people are all excuses.
You wanna point a finger--

1045
01:22:42,257 --> 01:22:44,919
-You goddamn son of a bitch.
-Gotta find that go-to guy.

1046
01:22:45,127 --> 01:22:47,095
You should've started
with a go-to girl, Jack.

1047
01:22:47,296 --> 01:22:48,558
-That cuts it.
-He's right.

1048
01:22:48,764 --> 01:22:50,095
What?

1049
01:22:50,466 --> 01:22:52,434
He's right. He is.

1050
01:22:55,337 --> 01:22:57,134
All of it.

1051
01:22:58,040 --> 01:23:03,068
We worked so hard for two years.
And I just went and threw it all away.

1052
01:23:11,520 --> 01:23:13,818
-Why did you stay with me?
-Kate, don't.

1053
01:23:15,457 --> 01:23:17,391
Don't what?

1054
01:23:17,893 --> 01:23:20,123
Tell the truth?

1055
01:23:21,597 --> 01:23:23,326
We can't buy back
what happened today.

1056
01:23:25,167 --> 01:23:27,135
We can't start over.

1057
01:23:28,137 --> 01:23:30,469
Do you think I look at myself,
at what I've become...

1058
01:23:30,672 --> 01:23:32,606
...and do you think I'm proud?

1059
01:23:33,809 --> 01:23:35,071
What do you want?

1060
01:23:36,478 --> 01:23:38,673
I don't know.

1061
01:23:40,649 --> 01:23:43,641
I guess I would like to go back
to the beginning and have you say...

1062
01:23:43,852 --> 01:23:46,753
...win or lose,
I could just be your daughter.

1063
01:23:52,060 --> 01:23:54,028
You came every day,
and you skated.

1064
01:23:56,165 --> 01:23:58,895
This must've been
like a nightmare for you.

1065
01:24:04,339 --> 01:24:07,502
I didn't know it was gonna
end up like this.

1066
01:24:13,982 --> 01:24:15,540
I'm sorry.

1067
01:24:20,722 --> 01:24:23,350
I'm so sorry. For everything.

1068
01:24:28,063 --> 01:24:30,293
Please excuse me.

1069
01:24:40,776 --> 01:24:42,869
I'm going for a walk.

1070
01:26:02,824 --> 01:26:05,657
Kate. What's this?

1071
01:26:07,796 --> 01:26:11,197
I'm going over with my father.
Anton has the other car.

1072
01:26:11,400 --> 01:26:13,300
He'll take you over
when you're ready to go.

1073
01:26:13,502 --> 01:26:17,131
-No, I'm talking about the bags.
-I'm catching the 6:30 flight tonight.

1074
01:26:17,339 --> 01:26:19,603
Tonight? After we skate?

1075
01:26:19,808 --> 01:26:21,469
The house is paid up
for two weeks...

1076
01:26:21,677 --> 01:26:24,703
-...so stay as long as you like.
-Kate, wait. What are you saying?

1077
01:26:24,913 --> 01:26:27,711
-lf this is about yesterday--
-I'm retiring.

1078
01:26:30,185 --> 01:26:31,379
What?

1079
01:26:34,923 --> 01:26:37,323
This afternoon is my final skate.

1080
01:26:38,393 --> 01:26:40,520
-Kate, come on--
-You'll be fine.

1081
01:26:42,197 --> 01:26:44,791
You won't have any trouble
finding another partner.

1082
01:26:47,936 --> 01:26:52,202
Of course, they won't have
my wonderful slap shot.

1083
01:26:54,242 --> 01:26:56,267
I gotta go get ready.

1084
01:27:45,460 --> 01:27:48,054
Beautiful extension.
Very classy.

1085
01:27:48,263 --> 01:27:49,662
Executed very nicely.

1086
01:27:49,865 --> 01:27:52,629
I hope they can keep it
going to the finish.

1087
01:28:04,746 --> 01:28:07,840
Neuman and Pekurovsky
looking well-positioned for a medal.

1088
01:28:08,050 --> 01:28:11,542
Still to skate are Smilkov-Brushkin
and Kate Moseley and Doug Dorsey.

1089
01:28:24,032 --> 01:28:27,001
Do you know what I think
would be wonderful?

1090
01:28:27,569 --> 01:28:32,131
If you would go out there today
and skate for these people...

1091
01:28:32,340 --> 01:28:35,070
...the way I have seen you skate.

1092
01:28:38,180 --> 01:28:40,740
Enjoy each other.

1093
01:29:04,639 --> 01:29:07,107
What's the matter?

1094
01:29:07,309 --> 01:29:08,276
Nothing.

1095
01:29:08,477 --> 01:29:11,378
-Are you all right?
-Fine.

1096
01:29:21,957 --> 01:29:23,720
Kate, I'm sorry.

1097
01:29:23,925 --> 01:29:26,416
My timing--
I know it stinks, but....

1098
01:29:26,628 --> 01:29:28,789
I just keep thinking
this thing with us....

1099
01:29:28,997 --> 01:29:30,259
It's gonna go away.

1100
01:29:30,465 --> 01:29:33,400
I keep thinking if I can just keep
moving and checking...

1101
01:29:33,602 --> 01:29:35,900
...I'll get clear, but....

1102
01:29:36,104 --> 01:29:37,969
Do you understand
what I'm telling you?

1103
01:29:38,173 --> 01:29:41,370
-I don't wanna fight anymore.
-No. I mean, yeah, I don't wanna fight.

1104
01:29:41,576 --> 01:29:43,874
-Look, we have to skate.
-This won't wait.

1105
01:29:44,079 --> 01:29:46,240
Kate, maybe I wasn't ready.
Maybe--

1106
01:29:46,448 --> 01:29:48,678
Maybe you didn't give me much
of a chance. Maybe--

1107
01:29:48,884 --> 01:29:51,751
I don't know. I just-- I just--

1108
01:29:51,953 --> 01:29:53,545
Nine-six.
Nine-three.

1109
01:29:56,424 --> 01:29:59,655
Kate, somewhere in the middle
of all this I fell in love with you.

1110
01:30:01,730 --> 01:30:04,198
You may take the ice.

1111
01:30:04,399 --> 01:30:08,062
I'm saying I love you.
I'm saying it out loud.

1112
01:30:20,115 --> 01:30:21,946
Don't say we're not right
for each other...

1113
01:30:22,150 --> 01:30:24,243
...because we may not be right
for anybody else.

1114
01:30:24,452 --> 01:30:27,819
-You have to go on.
-Will you shut up a minute.

1115
01:30:28,023 --> 01:30:31,117
It can't be any harder to stay together
than it was to stay apart.

1116
01:30:31,326 --> 01:30:33,260
-Thirty seconds.
-Will you wait a minute.

1117
01:30:35,163 --> 01:30:36,255
Kate.

1118
01:30:37,199 --> 01:30:39,497
I need you.

1119
01:30:41,503 --> 01:30:42,663
I need you.

1120
01:30:54,516 --> 01:30:56,313
We're doing the Pamchenko.

1121
01:30:57,052 --> 01:30:59,247
-What?
-Oh, you heard me.

1122
01:30:59,454 --> 01:31:01,615
Think I'm doing this
to get a program out of you?

1123
01:31:01,823 --> 01:31:03,222
You wanna win, don't you?

1124
01:31:03,925 --> 01:31:05,825
No. It's no good, Kate.
It's too dangerous.

1125
01:31:06,861 --> 01:31:09,227
Then we agreed.
We're putting it in.

1126
01:31:13,702 --> 01:31:14,930
-It's out.
-It's in.

1127
01:31:15,136 --> 01:31:16,125
-Out.
-ln.

1128
01:31:16,338 --> 01:31:17,600
-Out.
-ln.

1129
01:31:20,008 --> 01:31:22,340
-What difference does it make?
-The difference is...

1130
01:31:22,544 --> 01:31:25,035
...I'm in the mood to kick a little ass.

1131
01:33:05,914 --> 01:33:08,644
-You didn't have to.
-Yes, I did.

1132
01:33:09,517 --> 01:33:11,041
Why?

1133
01:33:12,721 --> 01:33:14,154
Because I love you.

1134
01:33:16,991 --> 01:33:19,357
Just remember
who said it first.

